HEADWORD: Dicksonia
<hw>Dicksonia</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <def>A genus of tree ferns of
temperate Australasia having bipinnatifid or tripinnatifid fronds and
usually marginal sori; in some classification systems it is placed in
the family <fam>Cyatheaceae</fam>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Dicksonia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
